Package ca.on.oicr.gsi.shesmu.runtime

Class ActionGenerator

java.lang.Object
ca.on.oicr.gsi.shesmu.runtime.ActionGenerator
All Implemented Interfaces:
RequiredServices
public abstract class ActionGenerator extends Object implements RequiredServices
Superclass for user-defined

This is the bridge interface between the Java code in the server and the compiled Shesmu script. The compiler will convert a Shesmu script into a subclass and can expect to call it using only what is defined in this class.

    • register

      public final void register()
      Add all Prometheus monitoring for this program.

      Only one Shemsu script may be active at any time, but multiple may be loaded in memory as part of compilation. Since duplicate Prometheus metrics are not permitted, Shesmu will unregister() the old ActionGenerator to remove its monitoring output, then connect the new one using register().

    • run

      public abstract void run(OliveServices consumer, InputProvider input)
      Call the action generator to process the input.
      Parameters:
      consumer - an output handler to collect and process actions as they are created; this may be called multiple times with duplicate input
      input - a generator of a stream of input from the outside world; this maybe called multiple times; the contents of the stream should remain the value-equivalent for each call. The order of the input and reference-equivalence are not required. That is, multiple calls do not have return the same objects, but should return ones with the same content. Duplicate items are permitted, but might be a problem for the Shesmu script.
